Consider the following class declaration.

```java
class Ticket
{
    private String name;
    private int count;

    public Ticket(String n, int c)
    {
        name = n;
        count = c;
    }

    public Ticket(String n)
    {
        name = n;
        count = 1;
    }

    public void add(int extra)
    {
        count += extra;
    }

    public String toString()
    {
        return name + ":" + count;
    }
}
```

What is printed by the following code segment?

```java
Ticket a = new Ticket("quiz", 2);
Ticket b = new Ticket("lab");
Ticket c = a;
c.add(3);
b = new Ticket("exam", b.toString().length());
System.out.println(a + " " + b + " " + c);
```

